Well I read the report on the info bits forum, but just thought I'd pop in here to comment.<br>
<br>
I'm glad your keeping going on this despite the apparent lack of acknowledgement from Mythic. Especially with a couple of other team leads moving on to the new classes.<br>
<br>
As usual the report was excellent. The only thing I would comment on is about the dmg add stacking problem. I know exactly what the problem is, so I understand it fine,  but I'm not sure your description may make it clear to mythic personal (pressuming they don't already know the problem, and if they do I'm shocked they've not done anything about it).<br>
<br>
I would suggest mentioning the more specific situation where the dmg stacking code works against midgards set up. I.E. When the shaman or runemasters damage add is less then half of the skalds one (which except for max dark spec runemasters this is almost always the case).<br>
<br>
Because Albions single target dmg adds are baseline they will never face this problem (unless some lowbie wiz/the decides to buff a higher level group) and because Wardens always favour the bubble chant to the dmg chant Hibernians don't tend to come across it. This makes this very much a Midgard problem and something I hope is in the runemaster and shaman reports as well as your own (mental note to check that).<br>
<br>
Anyway, I know you want to keep the sections brief, but I think it's worth clarifying the dmg stacking thing a bit (well mentioning that a single target dmg add of less then 1/2 the group chant will reduce overall dmg anyway).<br>
<br>
The rest of the report was perfect. I just wish Mythic would take notice of these problems. They could at least sort out FoG's. They've tweeked other realm skills so it's about time they looked at ours. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald>Team Skald</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1>General Discussion</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font> <!-- #EndEditable -->
